## 2. Mod Entrypoints

```java
// Main entrypoint (server + client, runs on both sides)
public class MyMod implements ModInitializer {
    public static final String MOD_ID = "mymod";
    public static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MOD_ID);

    @Override
    public void onInitialize() {
        // Register items, blocks, events, commands here
        ModItems.initialize();
        ModBlocks.initialize();
    }
}

// Client-only entrypoint
public class MyModClient implements ClientModInitializer {
    @Override
    public void onInitializeClient() {
        // Register client-side things: renderers, keybinds, HUD elements
    }
}
```

**Environment annotations** to restrict code to one side:
```java
@Environment(EnvType.CLIENT)  // Only compiled/run on client
@Environment(EnvType.SERVER)  // Only compiled/run on server
```

