## 5. Events (Fabric API)

Events are stored in static `EVENT` fields on callback interfaces. Register with `.register()`.

```java
// Register in onInitialize():

// Player hurts themselves when breaking blocks barehanded
AttackBlockCallback.EVENT.register((player, level, hand, pos, direction) -> {
    BlockState state = level.getBlockState(pos);
    if (!player.isSpectator() && player.getMainHandItem().isEmpty()
            && state.requiresCorrectToolForDrops()
            && level instanceof ServerLevel serverLevel) {
        player.hurtServer(serverLevel, level.damageSources().generic(), 1.0F);
    }
    return InteractionResult.PASS;
});

// Loot table modification (add items to vanilla loot tables)
LootTableEvents.MODIFY.register((key, tableBuilder, source, registries) -> {
    if (source.isBuiltin() && MY_TARGET_LOOT_ID.equals(key)) {
        tableBuilder.withPool(LootPool.lootPool().add(LootItem.lootTableItem(Items.EGG)));
    }
});

// Server tick
ServerTickEvents.END_SERVER_TICK.register(server -> { /* tick logic */ });
```

### Creating Custom Events
1. Define a callback `@FunctionalInterface`
2. Create an `Event<YourCallback>` instance via `EventFactory.createArrayBacked()`
3. Fire the event from a Mixin by calling `YOUR_EVENT.invoker().yourMethod(...)`

