## 6. Commands (Brigadier)

```java
// In ModInitializer.onInitialize() or a separate class:
CommandRegistrationCallback.EVENT.register((dispatcher, registryAccess, environment) -> {
    dispatcher.register(Commands.literal("mycommand")
        .then(Commands.argument("value", IntegerArgumentType.integer())
            .executes(context -> {
                int val = IntegerArgumentType.getInteger(context, "value");
                context.getSource().sendSuccess(
                    () -> Component.literal("Value: " + val), false);
                return 1;
            }))
        .executes(context -> {
            context.getSource().sendSuccess(
                () -> Component.literal("Called /mycommand"), false);
            return 1;
        }));
});
```

**Permission check**:
```java
.requires(source -> source.permissions().hasPermission(Permissions.COMMANDS_MODERATOR))
```

**Custom argument type**: implement `ArgumentType<T>`, register with `ArgumentTypeRegistry.registerArgumentType(...)`.

