## 7. Networking (Client ↔ Server)

Packets bridge the logical client and logical server. Even in singleplayer, an integrated server runs.
**Packet handlers execute on the network thread** — use `.execute()` to dispatch to the main thread.

### Define a Payload
```java
// A Record implementing CustomPacketPayload
public record MyPayload(BlockPos pos) implements CustomPacketPayload {
    public static final CustomPacketPayload.Type<MyPayload> TYPE =
        new CustomPacketPayload.Type<>(Identifier.fromNamespaceAndPath("mymod", "my_packet"));
    public static final StreamCodec<RegistryFriendlyByteBuf, MyPayload> CODEC =
        StreamCodec.composite(BlockPos.STREAM_CODEC, MyPayload::pos, MyPayload::new);
    @Override public Type<? extends CustomPacketPayload> type() { return TYPE; }
}
```

### Register & Send (Server → Client)
```java
// Registration (in onInitialize or onInitializeClient):
PayloadTypeRegistry.playS2C().register(MyPayload.TYPE, MyPayload.CODEC);

// Send from server:
ServerPlayNetworking.send(serverPlayer, new MyPayload(blockPos));

// Receive on client (in ClientModInitializer):
ClientPlayNetworking.registerGlobalReceiver(MyPayload.TYPE, (payload, context) -> {
    context.client().execute(() -> {
        // safe to access game state here
        BlockPos pos = payload.pos();
    });
});
```

### Register & Send (Client → Server)
```java
PayloadTypeRegistry.playC2S().register(MyPayload.TYPE, MyPayload.CODEC);

// Send from client:
ClientPlayNetworking.send(new MyPayload(blockPos));

// Receive on server:
ServerPlayNetworking.registerGlobalReceiver(MyPayload.TYPE, (payload, context) -> {
    context.player().server.execute(() -> {
        // server-side logic
    });
});
```

