## 8. Mixins

Mixins modify Minecraft's **compiled bytecode at runtime** before a class is loaded.
Only Java Mixins are supported (Kotlin requires compatibility layers).
MixinExtras is bundled since Fabric Loader 0.15 (v0.5.0 since Loader 0.17.0).

### Setup
1. Create `mymod.mixins.json` in `src/main/resources/`:
```json
{
  "required": true,
  "package": "com.example.mymod.mixin",
  "compatibilityLevel": "JAVA_21",
  "mixins": [],
  "client": ["ExampleClientMixin"],
  "injectors": { "defaultRequire": 1 }
}
```
2. Reference it in `fabric.mod.json` under `"mixins": ["mymod.mixins.json"]`

### Mixin Class Conventions
- Name: `TargetClassMixin` (e.g. `PlayerEntityMixin`)
- Make the class `abstract` → prevents accidental instantiation, no need to implement all methods
- Keep it package-private (not `public`)
- Never instantiate a Mixin class

```java
@Mixin(SomeVanillaClass.class)
abstract class SomeVanillaClassMixin {
    // injectors here
}
```

### Core Injector: `@Inject`

```java
// Inject at head of a void method
@Inject(method = "targetMethod()V", at = @At("HEAD"))
private void onTargetMethod(CallbackInfo ci) { /* ... */ }

// Inject at return and cancel (return early)
@Inject(method = "getValue()I", at = @At("RETURN"), cancellable = true)
private void modifyReturn(CallbackInfoReturnable<Integer> cir) {
    cir.setReturnValue(cir.getReturnValue() * 2);
}

// Inject before a specific method call
@Inject(method = "foo()V",
    at = @At(value = "INVOKE", target = "Lsome/Class;someMethod()V"))
private void beforeSomeMethod(CallbackInfo ci) { /* ... */ }

// Inject AFTER a method call (shift)
@Inject(method = "foo()V",
    at = @At(value = "INVOKE", target = "Lsome/Class;someMethod()V",
             shift = At.Shift.AFTER))
private void afterSomeMethod(CallbackInfo ci) { /* ... */ }
```

**Common `@At` values**: `HEAD`, `RETURN`, `TAIL`, `INVOKE`, `FIELD`, `NEW`

### `@Redirect` (use sparingly — hard incompatibility!)
```java
@Redirect(method = "foo()V",
    at = @At(value = "INVOKE", target = "Lsome/Class;someMethod(I)I"))
private int redirectMethod(SomeClass instance, int arg) {
    return MyClass.myAlternativeMethod(arg);
}
```
Prefer `@WrapOperation` or `@ModifyExpressionValue` from MixinExtras instead.

### MixinExtras (preferred for compatibility)
```java
// Modify return value compatibly
@ModifyReturnValue(method = "getValue()I", at = @At("RETURN"))
private int modifyReturnValue(int original) { return original * 2; }

// Wrap a method call
@WrapOperation(method = "foo()V",
    at = @At(value = "INVOKE", target = "Lsome/Class;someMethod()V"))
private void wrapSomeMethod(SomeClass instance, Operation<Void> original) {
    // pre-logic
    original.call(instance);
    // post-logic
}

// Capture local variables
@Inject(method = "foo()V", at = @At("INVOKE", target = "..."))
private void withLocal(CallbackInfo ci, @Local LocalRef<String> localRef) {
    localRef.set(localRef.get() + " modified");
}
```

### `@Accessor` / `@Invoker` (read/write private fields, call private methods)
```java
@Mixin(SomeClass.class)
public interface SomeClassAccessor {
    @Accessor("privateField")
    int getPrivateField();

    @Accessor("privateField")
    void setPrivateField(int value);

    @Invoker("privateMethod")
    void callPrivateMethod();
}
```

### `@Unique` — prevent naming conflicts
```java
@Unique
private int mymod$myCustomField = 0;
```

### Mixin Best Practices
- ✅ Prefer `@Inject` over `@Redirect` and **never** use `@Overwrite`
- ✅ Use MixinExtras (`@WrapOperation`, `@ModifyExpressionValue`) for compatible changes
- ✅ Annotate all custom fields/methods with `@Unique` and prefix with `modid$`
- ✅ Use events/Fabric API hooks before reaching for Mixins
- ✅ Make Mixin classes abstract and package-private
- ❌ Never copy Mixin examples verbatim — every case is different
- For lambdas: inspect bytecode (MCDev or javap) to find the synthetic method name

### Debugging Mixins
- MCDev plugin adds breakpoint support directly in Mixin classes
- Export mixins to inspect merged classes: add `-Dmixin.debug.export=true` to JVM args
- Use `CAPTURE_FAILHARD` when capturing locals for immediate crash on mismatch

