## 9. Access Wideners

Widen access to private/protected/final Minecraft members without reflection.

1. Create `mymod.accesswidener` in `src/main/resources/`:
```
accessWidener v2 named

accessible class net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass
accessible method net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass privateMethod ()V
accessible field net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass privateField I
mutable field net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass finalField I
extendable class net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass
extendable method net/minecraft/some/PrivateClass <init> ()V
```
2. Reference in `build.gradle`:
```groovy
loom { accessWidenerPath = file("src/main/resources/mymod.accesswidener") }
```
3. Reference in `fabric.mod.json`:
```json
"accessWidener": "mymod.accesswidener"
```

