## 11. Java OOP Essentials (for Fabric Modding)

### Core OOP Pillars
| Concept | Minecraft/Fabric Example |
|---|---|
| **Encapsulation** | `private` fields + getters/setters, Mixin `@Accessor` |
| **Inheritance** | `CustomBlock extends Block`, `CustomItem extends Item` |
| **Polymorphism** | `InteractionResult.PASS/SUCCESS`, override `use()` in items |
| **Abstraction** | `abstract class AbstractBlock`, interfaces like `BlockEntityProvider` |

### Key Java Concepts Used in Fabric
```java
// Generics - type-safe registries
public static <T extends Item> T register(String name, Function<Item.Properties, T> factory, ...) {}

// Functional interfaces + lambdas - events
AttackBlockCallback.EVENT.register((player, level, hand, pos, dir) -> { return InteractionResult.PASS; });

// Records - packet payloads (Java 16+)
public record MyPayload(BlockPos pos) implements CustomPacketPayload { ... }

// Sealed classes / Pattern matching instanceof
if (level instanceof ServerLevel serverLevel) { /* server-only */ }

// Static initialization pattern
public class ModItems {
    public static final Item MY_ITEM = register(...);
    public static void initialize() {} // triggers static init
}
```

### Java Collections in Minecraft
- `List<ItemStack>` – inventories, loot pools
- `Map<ResourceLocation, ...>` – registries
- `Set<BlockState>` – block state sets (tags)
- Use `ImmutableList`/`ImmutableMap` (Guava, bundled) for read-only data

### Common Patterns
```java
// Registry pattern (always use your MOD_ID as namespace)
Identifier.fromNamespaceAndPath(MOD_ID, "my_thing")

// Server-side check (CRITICAL - prevents desync)
if (level.isClientSide()) return InteractionResult.PASS;

// Ticks conversion: 20 ticks = 1 second
int threeSeconds = 3 * 20; // 60 ticks

// BlockPos manipulation
BlockPos front = player.blockPosition().relative(player.getDirection(), 10);
```

